        en: 'Case of platform operations — a radically different model from a restaurant.\n\nDeliveroo\'s operational tasks:\n• Aggregation: ~10,000 restaurant partners in Singapore with real-time menus, prices and availability\n• Order management: payment processing, routing and confirmation\n• Last-mile logistics: coordination of independent rider network\n• Data and algorithms: route optimisation, demand forecasting, surge pricing\n\nDifference from a restaurant: the restaurant transforms ingredients into food (physical conversion); Deliveroo transforms information into logistical coordination. Stores nothing — asset-light.\n\nBusiness model: two-sided marketplace. Commission % from restaurants + delivery fee from customers. Core asset = algorithm + rider network.\n\nExpansion advice:\n1. Deepen existing markets (dark kitchens) before expanding geographically\n2. Invest in dependability — promised vs. actual time is the main order-winner\n3. Diversify into grocery/quick commerce using existing logistics infrastructure'
